---
import { C, FONT } from "../infographicTokens";
---

<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 720 300" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
  <title>How SEER turns into a dollar figure on your bill</title>
  <desc>
    Annual cooling energy in kilowatt-hours equals the cooling BTU per hour times annual run hours,
    divided by SEER times 1,000. Multiply by your electricity rate to get the annual cooling cost.
    A higher SEER lowers the kilowatt-hours and therefore the bill.
  </desc>

  <rect x="8" y="8" width="704" height="284" rx="12" fill={C.panelBg} stroke={C.border} />
  <text x="24" y="36" fill={C.dark} font-family={FONT} font-size="14" font-weight="700">How SEER becomes a dollar figure</text>
  <text x="24" y="56" fill={C.muted} font-family={FONT} font-size="11">SEER sits in the denominator — raise it and the kilowatt-hours fall</text>

  <rect x="40" y="80" width="640" height="68" rx="10" fill={C.white} stroke={C.primary} stroke-width="1.4" />
  <text x="360" y="115" text-anchor="middle" fill={C.dark} font-family={FONT} font-size="15" font-weight="800">Annual kWh = (BTU/hr × run hours) ÷ (SEER × 1,000)</text>
  <text x="360" y="136" text-anchor="middle" fill={C.muted} font-family={FONT} font-size="10.5">cooling load × how long it runs, divided by efficiency</text>

  <rect x="40" y="164" width="640" height="56" rx="10" fill={C.primaryLight} stroke={C.primary} stroke-width="1.4" />
  <text x="360" y="198" text-anchor="middle" fill={C.dark} font-family={FONT} font-size="15" font-weight="800">Annual cost = Annual kWh × electricity rate ($/kWh)</text>

  <text x="40" y="248" fill={C.muted} font-family={FONT} font-size="10.5" font-weight="600">Run hours and rate are set by your climate and utility —</text>
  <text x="40" y="266" fill={C.muted} font-family={FONT} font-size="10.5" font-weight="600">SEER is the one term you control when you buy. Hotter climate + higher rate = bigger savings.</text>
</svg>
